\par 9. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9838106 NOTES ON CURRENCY CONVERSION}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10486579 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1576440 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10486579 
Those who, pursuant to the currency regulations, receive less than 100% of their income in Westmarks, state that they cannot meet their essential Westmark expenses. Above all, they find it difficult to produce the money for rent.
\par 
\par Independent trade
smen, artisans, teachers and other groups of persons for whom no provision has yet been made in the change-over regulations, are urging that their position should be made quite clear as quickly as possible, since, as they state, their livelihood is being 
directly threatened.
\par 
\par Hotels, hairdressers and BVG transport services report a further drop in the number of patrons. The population considers it to be unjustified for electricity and gas charges to be paid in Westmarks from the 1st April, since it is
 a question of payment for consumption prior to the currency change-over.
\par 
\par A reduction of postal fees and adjustment of postage rates to those in the Western Zones are also desired.
\par 
\par The exchange of money by persons living in a Western Sector but working in Eastern Berlin was in the general opinion badly organised, and in many cases took several hours to complete.
\par 
\par Individual firms have taken to reducing wages and salaries by 10-20% which has led to protests on the part of workers who are calling at the Price Office to obtain information on the wage stop.
\par 
\par Payments of unemployment assistance are unanimously said to be unpunctual and are causing great hardship to the persons concerned. They claim they are often 5-6 weeks without money.
\par 
\par In
 order to alleviate somewhat the shortage of money during this month, various firms and undertakings (including the Magistrat) granted advance payments before Easter against salaries due at the end of the month, these payments were welcomed by the majorit
y concerned.
\par 
\par J.E. Dixon 
\par P.O.R.O.
\par HQ CCG (BE) 
\par B.A.O.R.2
